SIMPLE: hostler
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hostler
<hw>Hos"tler</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>hosteler</ets>, <ets>osteler</ets>, innkeeper, OF.
<ets>hostelier</ets>, F. <ets>h⟦ocir⟧telier</ets>. See <er>Hostel</er>,
and cf. <er>Hospitaler</er>, <er>Hosteler</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>An innkeeper. <mark>[Obs.]</mark> See <er>Hosteler</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The person who has the care of horses at an inn or
stable; hence, any one who takes care of horses; a groom; -- so called
because the innkeeper formerly attended to this duty in
person.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Railroad)</fld> <def>The person who takes charge of
a locomotive when it is left by the engineer after a trip.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hostless</ent>⟦br⟧
